{"key":"post-8648422","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8648422</id>\n<content>If you don't have scales or empty syringes, you probably also don't have petri dishes, a flowhood or good glovebox, surgical masks and gloves, scalpels, etc., that are all important for agar isolations.&amp;nbsp; Get your supplies together first.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Everyone with a nickel and a ruler has a scale.&amp;nbsp; Balance a ruler over a fulcrum at the 6&quot; mark, and place a nickel at the 11&quot; mark and your powder at the 1&quot; mark.&amp;nbsp; When it balances, you have 5 grams of product.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8648428</next>\n<prev>8648406</prev>\n<first>8647458</first>\n<last>8650425</last>\n<when>1216345387</when>\n<utime>07/18/08 04:43 AM</utime>\n</post>"}